h3cDomain.name: h3cDomain
h3cDomain.contactinfo: Platform Team Beijing Institute H3C Tech, Inc. Http://www.h3c.com E-mail:support@h3c.com
h3cDomain.description: The MIB module is used for managing domain.

H3cModeOfDomainScheme.name: H3cModeOfDomainScheme
H3cModeOfDomainScheme.description: The scheme mode of the domain. none: indicates the domain has no scheme. local:indicates the domain will use local-server as a scheme. radius:indicates the domain will use radius scheme. tacacs:indicates the domain will use tacacs scheme.

H3cAAATypeDomainScheme.name: H3cAAATypeDomainScheme
H3cAAATypeDomainScheme.description: The service type of the server.

H3cAccessModeofDomainScheme.name: H3cAccessModeofDomainScheme
H3cAccessModeofDomainScheme.description: The access mode of the domain.

h3cDomainDefault.name: h3cDomainDefault
h3cDomainDefault.description: Specifies default domain on the equipment. Default value is 'system'.

h3cDomainInfoEntry.name: h3cDomainInfoEntry
h3cDomainInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a domain.

h3cDomainName.name: h3cDomainName
h3cDomainName.description: An index uniquely identifies a domain.

h3cDomainState.name: h3cDomainState
h3cDomainState.description: The state of the domain, which reflects whether the domain is active. Default value is active.

h3cDomainMaxAccessNum.name: h3cDomainMaxAccessNum
h3cDomainMaxAccessNum.description: The maximum number which the domain allows to access. If the value is set to 0, the access limit will be disabled.

h3cDomainVlanAssignMode.name: h3cDomainVlanAssignMode
h3cDomainVlanAssignMode.description: The vlan assignment mode. The mode SHOULD be the same as the mode of corresponding server. 1 (integer) - Integer Vlan assignment mode. 2 (string) - String Vlan assignment mode. 3 (vlanlist) - VLAN-List Vlan assignment mode. The default value is integer.

h3cDomainIdleCutEnable.name: h3cDomainIdleCutEnable
h3cDomainIdleCutEnable.description: The idle cut control. Setting this attribute to true, the connection will be cut when the flow is less than h3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow and lasts h3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime. Default value is false.

h3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime.name: h3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime
h3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime.description: The maximal time of idle-cut. The unit is minute. If the value of h3cDomainIdleCutEnable is false, the value of h3cDomainIdleCutMaxTime is meaningless.

h3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow.name: h3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow
h3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow.description: The minimal flow of idle-cut. The unit is byte. If the value of h3cDomainIdleCutEnable is false, the value of h3cDomainIdleCutMinFlow is meaningless.

h3cDomainMessengerEnable.name: h3cDomainMessengerEnable
h3cDomainMessengerEnable.description: The messenger service control. If set h3cDomainMessengerEnable to true, h3cDomainMessengerLimitTime and h3cDomainMessengerSpanTime must be set to valid values. Default value is false.

h3cDomainMessengerLimitTime.name: h3cDomainMessengerLimitTime
h3cDomainMessengerLimitTime.description: The messenger service limit time. The unit is minute. If the value of h3cDomainMessengerEnable is false, the value of h3cDomainMessengerLimitTime is meaningless.

h3cDomainMessengerSpanTime.name: h3cDomainMessengerSpanTime
h3cDomainMessengerSpanTime.description: The messenger service span time. The unit is minute. It must be a multiple of 5. If the value of h3cDomainMessengerEnable is false, the value of h3cDomainMessengerSpanTime is meaningless.

h3cDomainSelfServiceEnable.name: h3cDomainSelfServiceEnable
h3cDomainSelfServiceEnable.description: The self service control. If set h3cDomainSelfServiceEnable to true, h3cDomainSelfServiceURL must be set to a valid value. Default value is FALSE.

h3cDomainSelfServiceURL.name: h3cDomainSelfServiceURL
h3cDomainSelfServiceURL.description: Self-service URL(Uniform Resource Locator) of the domain.

h3cDomainAccFailureAction.name: h3cDomainAccFailureAction
h3cDomainAccFailureAction.description: Defines the action that authentication should be taken if authentication succeeds but the associated accounting start fails. 1 (ignore) - treat as authentication success; ignore accounting start failure. 2 (reject) - treat as authentication failed if corresponding accounting start fails. Default value is reject.

h3cDomainRowStatus.name: h3cDomainRowStatus
h3cDomainRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To destroy an existent row, the domain of the row MUST NOT be used by user.

h3cDomainCurrentAccessNum.name: h3cDomainCurrentAccessNum
h3cDomainCurrentAccessNum.description: The current access number of the domain.

h3cDomainSchemeTable.name: h3cDomainSchemeTable
h3cDomainSchemeTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing schemes of all domains.

h3cDomainSchemeEntry.name: h3cDomainSchemeEntry
h3cDomainSchemeEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IP pool of a domain

h3cDomainSchemeIndex.name: h3cDomainSchemeIndex
h3cDomainSchemeIndex.description: The scheme index of domain, which is an identifier of a domain scheme.

h3cDomainSchemeMode.name: h3cDomainSchemeMode
h3cDomainSchemeMode.description: The scheme mode of the domain. Setting h3cDomainSchemeMode to none(1) indicates the domain has none scheme. Setting h3cDomainSchemeMode to local(2) indicates the domain will use local-server as a scheme. Setting h3cDomainSchemeMode to radius(3) or tacacs(4) indicates the domain will use radius or tacacs scheme. If set h3cDomainSchemeMode to radius(3) or tacacs(4), h3cDomainAuthSchemeName and h3cDomainAcctSchemeName must be set to valid values. And if h3cDomainSchemeMode is set to none(1) or local(2), the value of h3cDomainAuthSchemeName and h3cDomainAcctSchemeName will be ignored.

h3cDomainAuthSchemeName.name: h3cDomainAuthSchemeName
h3cDomainAuthSchemeName.description: The authentication scheme name of domain. If h3cDomainSchemeMode is set to radius or tacacs, the h3cDomainAuthSchemeName must be configured with a valid value.

h3cDomainAcctSchemeName.name: h3cDomainAcctSchemeName
h3cDomainAcctSchemeName.description: The accounting scheme name of the domain. If h3cDomainSchemeMode is set to radius or tacacs, the h3cDomainAcctSchemeName must be configured with a valid value.

h3cDomainSchemeRowStatus.name: h3cDomainSchemeRowStatus
h3cDomainSchemeRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and createAndGo, destroy operation. To create a new row, h3cDomainSchemeMode must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the scheme of the row MUST NOT be used by user.

h3cDomainSchemeAAAName.name: h3cDomainSchemeAAAName
h3cDomainSchemeAAAName.description: The scheme name of the domain, whether the scheme represents accounting, authentication or authorization references the object h3cDomainSchemeAAAType. The value of the object must be valid if the value of h3cDomainSchemeMode is radius or tacacs, the value of the object will be ignored if the value of h3cDomainSchemeMode is none or local. If the domain has no scheme, there will be a null string. If this object is supported, the objects h3cDomainAuthSchemeName and h3cDomainAcctSchemeName will be ignored.

h3cDomainSchemeAccessMode.name: h3cDomainSchemeAccessMode
h3cDomainSchemeAccessMode.description: The access mode of the domain scheme.

h3cDomainIpPoolTable.name: h3cDomainIpPoolTable
h3cDomainIpPoolTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing IP pools of all domains.

h3cDomainIpPoolEntry.name: h3cDomainIpPoolEntry
h3cDomainIpPoolEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an IP pool of a domain.

h3cDomainIpPoolNum.name: h3cDomainIpPoolNum
h3cDomainIpPoolNum.description: The number of IP pool, which is an identifier of an IP pool.

h3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType.name: h3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType
h3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddrType.description: The low IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of IP pool.

h3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr.name: h3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr
h3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr.description: The low IP address of IP pool.

h3cDomainIpPoolLen.name: h3cDomainIpPoolLen
h3cDomainIpPoolLen.description: The length of IP pool. Default value is 1.

h3cDomainIpPoolRowStatus.name: h3cDomainIpPoolRowStatus
h3cDomainIpPoolRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which supports active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To create a new row, h3cDomainIpPoolNum and h3cDomainIpPoolLowIpAddr must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the IP pool of this row MUST NOT be used by user.
